For the broth, put all the ingredients in a large saucepan and add 2 litres/3Â½ pint water and bring to the boil. Simmer for 3 hours before straining through muslin cloth.Prepare the squid by scoring it four times on each side before cutting into long strips.Cut most of the wild leaves into small pieces but leave some of the larger ones whole.Mix the squid with the rapeseed oil.Put the squid into a serving bowl and lay some of the bigger leaves around the edge. Ladle over the warm broth and finish with the chopped leaves and the garnish ingredients.